This is one my favorite songs.. As I see lot of comments on asking for meaning..  I am copying and pasting the translation I tried earlier.. This song is a woman's plea to husband, who took home for granted and obsessed with his achievements of the outside world.   Hero starts by addressing his dad's mishaps and if only Dad had heard the plea of his wife (hero's mother), things would have been different. The plea (song) goes like this.. I let go of my sleep to remain wide-eyed.. to lay longing gaze on your return path  ... Please return home.. but be mindful of discomforts in your path.. Return for the sake of my broken heart For the sake of your favorite dish  Oh my hubby.. its been ages since I saw you to my heart's content The cozy darkness, the tasty small talk,  The warmth of the fire, the cozy blanket await you.. Singing her heart out is the cute cuckoo bird,  for whose sake you should come back.. (bird refers to self here) My heart is distraught that you are out of reach... don't disregard the heart that cares for you like you were a child.. don't destroy my fate by being disconnected.. for the sake of our marriage, please return ... Your stature is bigger .. but its too small for me to trace you.. worried if you toiling in the heat or drenched in blood.. concerned if you are hungry or helpless.. At least for the sake of  (y)our kid.. please come back.. Oh my hubby.. its been ages since I saw you to my heart's content
